Affordable accommodation

Glossy brochures focus on ultra-swish resorts , but French Polynesia actually has a pretty wide range of accommodation options . You can keep lodging costs down by staying in small guesthouses and pensions -LRB- homestays -RRB- that are sprinkled around the islands . They 're nothing glam or ostentatious , just modest operations that blend perfectly into the tropical surroundings . At the cheaper end of the scale -LRB- around US$ 80 a double -RRB- , they consist of simple , local-style bungalows with cold showers and thin walls . Upmarket versions -LRB- plan on US$ 100-120 -RRB- have lots of amenities and are more comfortable .

